4:
Master! Master, wake up! The village
is on fire!
7:
Huh? Oh, that. Relax, will you? The
villagers'll come crying soon.
9:
You have to let them sweat it out a
bit, otherwise they'll cheap out on
the reward.
12:
Ugh, you're a nasty piece of work,
Master...
18:
Hehehe... There they are. Time to get
to work.
22:
A fire sprite, you say? How truly
awful...
25:
Yes. It's burned through our food
stores. If this goes on, our village will
starve!
27:
I hate to hear it, but well... I'm a busy
guy.
30:
Gianini, what's my schedule like
today?
33:
Your... what? You don't have
any—gah!
37:
What's that? I have to clear out
golems in an ancient ruin and
escort a noble lady? My day's
looking packed.
40:
L-Lord Mordiaga, please don't
abandon us in our time of need!
43:
If you're that desperate, then I'm
sure you know what to do.
45:
Of course! We'll give you anything
you want!
48:
How generous of you. Let's see... Give
me that antique lamp.
51:
You want that old thing? By all
means, take it!
54:
Now that that's settled, let's get to
work, Gianini!
62: What a bore. That was too easy.
65:
Wheeze... That's because I did all the
work...
67:
You looked so heroic putting out the
fires, Lord Gianini!
73:
You, fire sprite. Loser's got to do
what the winner says, eh?
77:
Hehehe, it's an offer you can't
refuse... Welcome to your new home!
82:
Heh, and there we have it—one
magical item containing a sprite.
84:
An old lamp like this fits the part too.
This'll sell for a pretty penny.
87:
That's what you were after? Ugh, I
can't believe I thought you were
doing something kind for once! You
tricked me!
89:
You're an idiot for thinking it in the
first place. Come on, we're done
here.
93:
Hehehe, thanks to the power of
sprites, my life's turned from a
desert into an oasis.
95:
Gianini's lamp will stay with me for a
good long time. Be stupid to let such
a useful tool go to waste, after all.
